history.content:
Historically, prereq for cs isn't enforced, except for some 1-unit self-pace classes. This fall, many cs courses are switching over to informally enforcing prereqs. This means that the system will not block you from enrolling but the professor have the right to drop you during the first few weeks if they see that you don't have the prereq.

Some professors don't drop students even if they are missing a prerequisite, like with DS100 historically. But it's up to the professor so you should reach out to them to see if they are planning to manually enforce some of the prerequisite.

I am just trying to get some idea of the order of upper divs I want to take, and was wondering if prereqs like 61c for 186 is enforced, for example? If not, are there any other upper division courses where the prereqs are really enforced?
history.subject: are there any courses where the prereqs are enforced? If so, which ones?
